# Git commits — no Cursor co-author

When staging or committing in this repo:

- Do **not** pass `--trailer "Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>"` or any similar `Co-authored-by` trailer for Cursor.
- Use a plain commit only, for example: `git commit -m "your message"`.
- Do not suggest or document commands that include Cursor co-author trailers.

The repository uses `.githooks/prepare-commit-msg` (via `git config core.hooksPath .githooks`) to strip accidental Cursor co-author lines from the commit message file.
